#: course/lesson-2-your-first-error/lesson.tres:14
msgid "When you program, you are bound to run into errors. Tons of them."
msgstr "编程时，你不可避免地会遇到错误，而且会非常多。"

msgid ""
"But you shouldn't worry! On the computer, [b]errors are a good thing[/b]."
msgstr "但你不用为此担心！在计算机的世界里，[b]错误其实是好事[/b]。"

msgid ""
"You will encounter errors, and [i]that's okay[/i]: every programmer does. "
"Especially professionals."
msgstr ""
"你会遇到错误，但这[i]没什么大不了[/i]：每个程序员都会遇到，专业程序员尤其如此"
"。"

msgid ""
"At school, maybe you learned that mistakes are a bad thing. When you code "
"something, it's not the case: [b]errors help you write correct programs[/b] "
"because they show you what is wrong in your programs."
msgstr ""
"在学校里，你可能学过犯错是坏事。但在写代码时，情况并非如此：[b]错误能帮你写出"
"正确的程序[/b]，因为它会告诉你程序哪里出了问题。"

#: course/lesson-2-your-first-error/lesson.tres:30
msgid ""
"A code error looks like this. It's a message that tells you some bit of your "
"code doesn't work."
msgstr "代码错误长这样。它是一条消息，告诉你代码的某一部分不能正常工作了。"

#: course/lesson-2-your-first-error/lesson.tres:48
msgid "Making errors friendlier"
msgstr "让错误更友好"

#: course/lesson-2-your-first-error/lesson.tres:50
msgid ""
"Error messages can look a bit cryptic. This is because they're designed by "
"programmers, for trained programmers."
msgstr ""
"错误信息看起来可能有点晦涩难懂。这是因为它们是由程序员为训练有素的程序员设计"
"的。"

msgid ""
"We added an error translator in this app that will help you get started."
msgstr "我们在这个应用中添加了一个错误翻译器，帮你更好地入门。"

msgid ""
"It shows you why an error happens and what the message means. It also gives "
"you some tips on how to fix it."
msgstr "它会告诉你错误产生的原因以及错误信息的含义，还会给你一些修复建议。"

#: course/lesson-2-your-first-error/lesson.tres:74
msgid ""
"Error messages are designed on purpose by fellow programmers who came before "
"you. They anticipated you might have specific issues and wanted to help you "
"fix them."
msgstr ""
"错误信息是在你之前的程序员特意设计的。他们预见到你可能会遇到某些特定的问题，"
"并希望帮助你解决这些问题。"

msgid ""
"You shouldn't think of errors as failures. They are like mentors helping you "
"from the past. Importantly, errors won't break your computer. At least not "
"with GDScript because it's a pretty safe language."
msgstr ""
"你不应该把错误看作失败。它们就像是从过去来帮助你的导师。更重要的是，错误不会"
"搞坏你的电脑。至少在 GDScript 中不会，因为它是一门相当安全的语言。"

msgid ""
"Ultimately, you want to fix all the errors in your program. Understanding "
"what is causing the errors, with the help of error messages, is key to "
"fixing them."
msgstr ""
"归根结底，你是想修复程序中的所有错误。而借助错误信息来弄清楚错误产生的原因，"
"正是修复它们的关键。"

#: course/lesson-2-your-first-error/lesson.tres:86
msgid "Are error messages a good or a bad thing in code?"
msgstr "代码中的错误信息是好事还是坏事？"

#: course/lesson-2-your-first-error/lesson.tres:89
msgid "Yes, error messages are here to help you!"
msgstr "是的，错误信息是来帮助你的！"

msgid ""
"Pay attention to them, and do your best to read and understand them. With "
"experience, you'll learn to make your code work more reliably thanks to "
"error messages."
msgstr ""
"请留意这些信息，尽力阅读并理解它们。随着经验的积累，你会学会借助错误信息让自"
"己的代码更加稳定可靠。"

#: course/lesson-2-your-first-error/lesson.tres:92
msgid "They're bad: error messages are always bad."
msgstr "坏事：错误信息总是很糟糕。"

#: course/lesson-2-your-first-error/lesson.tres:92
msgid "They're good: they're here to help."
msgstr "好事：它们是来帮忙的。"

#: course/lesson-2-your-first-error/lesson.tres:102
msgid ""
"Okay, let's see an error in action. Once again, click the [i]Practice[/i] "
"button below to face your first real error."
msgstr ""
"好了，让我们来看一个实际操作中的错误。再次点击下方的[i]练习[/i]按钮，来面对你"
"的第一个真正的错误。"

#: course/lesson-2-your-first-error/lesson.tres:110
msgid "Fix Your First Error"
msgstr "修复你的第一个错误"

#: course/lesson-2-your-first-error/lesson.tres:111
msgid "This code is incorrect and will cause an error when you try to run it."
msgstr "这段代码有误，运行时会引发一个错误。"

msgid ""
"The code defines an empty function named [code]this_code_is_wrong[/code]."
msgstr "这段代码定义了一个名为 [code]this_code_is_wrong[/code] 的空函数。"

msgid ""
"To work, the function should use the [code]return[/code] keyword. But this "
"keyword is currently inside a comment, which the computer ignores."
msgstr ""
"要让它正常工作，函数需要使用 [code]return[/code] 关键字。但这个关键字目前写在"
"了注释里，计算机会忽略它。"

msgid "Test the current code by pressing the [i]Run[/i] button."
msgstr "按下[i]运行[/i]按钮来测试当前代码。"

msgid "Then, remove the comment sign (#) to make the code valid."
msgstr "然后，移除注释符号（#），让代码变得有效。"

msgid ""
"Be careful not to remove the spacing before [code]return[/code]! Otherwise, "
"that'll cause another error. You may try that too, if you feel like it."
msgstr ""
"注意别把 [code]return[/code] 前面的空格也删掉了！不然就会引发另一个错误。如果"
"你想试试，也可以故意这么做。"

#: course/lesson-2-your-first-error/lesson.tres:132
msgid "There's an error in this code. We need you to fix it!"
msgstr "这段代码中有一个错误，需要你来修复它！"

#: course/lesson-2-your-first-error/lesson.tres:136
msgid "Your First Error"
msgstr "你的第一个错误"
